![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/999944a5-49d9-45ef-8861-2b2a6a9f0621/20240916_170835.jpg?format=original)

CM Punk opens RAW by saying he didn't mean to make a mortal enemy when he came back to WWE but he apparently has in Drew McIntyre.

Punk says Drew made a mistake in not finishing the job. But now things are different. People ask Punk how many Hell in a Cell matches does he actually have left in him?

The honest answer is zero. His family has asked him not to do this and an angel on his shoulder is begging him not to do this.

But he wants everyone to know why he's going to do it anyway. If you push Punk far enough he can become the devil himself. And now the devil is here.

The devil in Punk's heart tells Punk this only ends at Hell in a Cell. The same heart that Drew McIntyre swore he would make stop beating.

But Punk isn't going to promise that he can kill Drew McIntyre. He can only promise that Drew MCINTYRE is going to have to kill PUNK because Punk is prepared to die and if this is the end, his career was great. So be it.

If Drew McIntyre is prepared the way Punk is, then Punk will see McIntyre in hell.

